text:
Merry late Christmas and early happy new year, Goomba.  Hope you are doing well.  Already did a lengthy member post but thought of a more abridged version to help you just a few hours after posting that one and it took me a while to post it here.  Thought I might as well share it since you clearly wanted to get more than you could do done this year and I think this idea could help streamline those efforts and focus on getting them completed.  I‚Äôm not sure of your current situation but this idea is flexible for you, is community driven and should help with stuff like: playing games you want to play, games you want to beat, games you want to return to, playing rage games, learning new songs for karaoke, creative streams, ASMR, celebrating milestones, member streams, collabs and whatever ideas you can think of.   This will act as a support along with the behind-the-scenes stuff you do that we won‚Äôt get to see till its final release.   We want to make all your crazy ideas come to fruition.  If you need any help to make it happen, then all you need to do is ask.

- Be well rested before stream since most streams are cut short because of being sleep deprived.  This also goes for games that were near completion as well that you haven't gone back to.
- Have a soft schedule of how many streams you want to do that week and stick to it.
- Collab streams, special events, unarchived karaoke or song release can be either be  a part or not part of the set soft schedule for those weeks depending on time constraints.
- One portion of that schedule is for games or whatever streams you want to do and the other is voted by the chumbies.
- Discuss possible streams to do near the end of a stream before the next stream or create a community post to discuss possible games to play or other stream ideas that can be done.
- If you want to do this long term, might I suggest a huge checklist.  Make a huge list of what you want to do for that year and add to it as you get ideas along the way.  Both you and the chumbies can contribute to this list.  This goes games or any other stream ideas or anything else I might‚Äôve not considered possible doing.  Ask friends or us for advice to make it happen or refine the idea if its a long term project.
- By making a list, adding and checking them off as you go along, I think you'll inch closer to getting the things you want done sooner because you are focused on the items on the list.
- Make a poll for the vote portion of the schedule and majority vote decides what you do that next stream.  You see us mentioning games we want you to play or going back to old playthroughs many times to beat but are unsure if there is interest in them since there has been a long gap of time since they were last mentioned or played.  I'm pretty sure we can prove that if we get to vote to show you that we want to see them no matter how long its been.
- Votes for things that might take a little more work to do than a game stream like what you did for Big Brain Games, those can be pushed to next week or two to be done at a later selected stream time.  For these types of streams, you can limit it to being able to do them 1 to 2 times in a month.
- 2nd most voted that is a game, if the creative stream wins the vote will act as chumbie voted stream for that week while you work on getting the creative stream done behind-the-scenes to stream it at a later date.
- If for whatever reason you can‚Äôt make the designated stream for that week, release a short instead similar to what you did with the elf video.  Either a short edited video or YouTube short.  Doing this should reduce long gaps between streams.  You can stack some beforehand for emergencies.
- You could also make shorts without the obligation to be a stream filler along with the set soft schedule for the week.
- That stream you couldn‚Äôt do that was replaced with a short will be delayed to the next available stream that isn‚Äôt a chumbie voted one.
- If you want to learn new songs for karaoke without just doing the same old songs, how about make a community post to request some song names instead of asking for it during the karaoke stream.  That way you have time to check them out, see if you like it and have enough time to practice it before the karaoke stream.  Maybe set this up a week or more before the actual karaoke.
- Expanding on that idea you had for a Pokemon endurance stream, how about for new games that come out that you aren‚Äôt sure you‚Äôll do more than 1 part for, do an endurance stream of it to get a good chunk of playtime into and get a better grasp if you‚Äôll continue playing or not.  Limit this to 1 to 2 times a month.
- Endurance stream also can be applied to finishing a bunch of games or returning to games you don‚Äôt think will bring in many views as a solo stream for the day.  If you can't stream the different games into a single VOD because of conflicting perms, then just make a bunch of separate streams in a single day with a break between them before the next one starts.  30 minutes to 1 hour might be enough.  You could also use this for games to go back to which multiple endings that you didn't get to see.
- You know how in some horror game streams, there is usually a collab partner that is there for emotional support?  I think you could also apply that idea to games that may be hard for you like Elden Ring or games that aren't usually your style of game to act as emotional support for you or as a coach to help you get through the game.
- For the list idea, if you have an idea that is crazy far-out that you don't think you can reasonable do more than the once or it's an out of left field game choice that you aren't sure you'll like but still gets voted for, you can reduce that to being selectable 1 time out of the whole year.  We know you want to try different things instead of just doing the same old all the time so this should limit over-burdening you.  You can apply a # limit to anything on the list or replenish it if you feel more comfortable doing them again.
- Here's a suggestion for a big branch or cross branch collab if you want to do it.  I already gave my idea of how to better the Big Brain Games in the video if you might want to continue that in the future with episode 2.  To lessen workload for you, how about a big WWE2k22 stream and all participants will create their own characters for them to be used in that tournament.  Between all of EN only or add in all of ID and if you are ambitious, some of JP.  Different rules for each match if possible.  Also, the participants will act as co-stars with you in commentary for matches that don't involve their own created character.  You get to collab with your senpai and kohai more and get more back-and-forth talk compared to the last Myth Night you did where it was you doing everything.  I remember Miko being interested in doing one with you way back so it might be a good start to doing big collabs for you to get used to doing some more in the future.

I hope this is helpful to you.  Use it all or parts of it to help with your time management.  Even though I give specific instructions, the ideas should be able to be applied to any other idea you can come up with.  This is more of a guideline to format your ideas and projects to work on them better.  You give so much for us but it hasn‚Äôt seem like you‚Äôve gotten much you want done in return.  I know you are busy at times but all we want is for you to enjoy yourself.  You haven‚Äôt had time to celebrate yourself to the fullest for the milestones you achieved thus far with whatever is taking your time right now.  I think I speak for most chumbies here that we want to make your dreams come true.  If you need helping hand to do it, we are willing to offer a guiding hand to accomplish it.   Don't doubt yourself.  You beat that cat rage game and DMC3 with perseverance and I think you can apply that same dedication to anything you set your mind to.

text: Well Gura, I don't expect this to be read, but I've said it before, and I'll say it again, communicating when these breaks happen is important! text:
Hey Gura, i'm not sure if you will actually see this, and I don't really have much to add to the various sentiments that are already in these comments, but I feel like I might as well throw in my 2 cents if only to get it off my chest.

I really wish you were more communicative about these breaks and your general schedule for streaming. Of course, that is only a wish, I wont claim that we are owed anything or that you need to stream according to our wishes, but it's really tough just not knowing what to expect. If this is the way it will be from now on, please tell us. It may not be ideal, but the complaints from the frustrated shrimps aren't going to stop until you take a stance on it. And if you are still trying to get better at communication or stream consistency but there is just stuff that keeps getting in the way, that's great and we'll be patient and gracious, but please tell us that you're trying. 
Right now we are all in a state of limbo with nothing but speculation between ourselves. The people who are frustrated are just going back and forth with the people who are defending you and with no input from you, it's not going to change anytime soon.
I choose to believe that you enjoy streaming. I choose to believe that you don't secretly resent us. And I choose to believe that this is a temporary thing. However, the longer these problems fester without you addressing it, the harder it is to believe these things.
All this being said, to the people lashing out, or anyone who is seriously hurting because of all this, we have work to do in our lives as well in order to sort our priorities for our own benefit. I feel like the phrase 'touch grass' is way more demeaning and belittling than it really should be, because it really is legitimate advice, taking a walk and being outside really does help. Try to actually do other stuff you enjoy or try some things you haven't ever done. In order to move on, you have to move on. You're not going to think your way into a better headspace, you have to do stuff. (at least that's my experience)

Overall though, I really do hope this is a passing phase. For both Gura and the community. Whether the end of the tunnel for Gura is more streams, more communication, or just Gura being happy with whatever she's doing, I hope we can all be happy and healthy and well adjusted in a community that hopefully can come out stronger from this.
